Enclosing class:
AbstractObject3DSpace
public class AbstractObject3DSpace.Abstract3DLocation
extends java.lang.Object
implements Object3DLocation, Drawable

A data structure holding an object and the x and y coordinates of that object. Note that the instance variables obj, x and y are public and so they may be accessed directly e.g 

   Abstract2DLocation ol = new Abstract2DLocation(someObj, 3, 3);
   Agent a = (Agent)ol.obj;
   int xLocl = ol.x;
   ...
However, changing these x and y coordinates does not effect the actual object coordinates in any way.

Abstract2DLocation overrides equals and will return true when the object and the x and y coordinates are equal.
